nd why</span></strong></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Right to request deletion of your data</span></strong></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Right to opt-out of sale (we don’t sell data)</span></strong></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Right to non-discrimination for exercising privacy rights</span></strong></p></li></ul><h3><strong><span>To Exercise Your Rights:</span></strong></h3><p><strong><span>Please email us at privacy@playvio.io with your request. We may need to verify your identity before processing it.</span></strong></p><p><strong><span>We respond to all valid requests within 30 days, or as required by applicable law.</span></strong></p><h2><strong><span>10. Children\'s Privacy (COPPA Compliance)</span></strong></h2><p><strong><span>PlayVio.io is not directed at children under the age of 13.</span></strong></p><p><strong><span>We do </span><span>not knowingly collect personal data from children</span><span> without verifiable parental consent. If we become aware that we have unknowingly collected data from a minor, we will promptly delete such information.</span></strong></p><p><strong><span>If you\'re a parent or guardian and believe your child has interacted with our site inappropriately, please contact us immediately at privacy@playvio.io.</span></strong></p><h2><strong><span>11. Data Security</span></strong></h2><p><strong><span>We take reasonable administrative, technical, and physical measures to safeguard your information from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or alteration.</span></strong></p><p><strong><span>Security measures include:</span></strong></p><ul><li><p><strong><span>HTTPS encryption</span></strong></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Firewall and server-side protection</span></strong></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Regular vulnerability scans</span></strong></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Limited access controls for staff</span></strong></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>However, no online platform is 100% secure. You use the site at your own risk, and we recommend avoiding submission of sensitive personal data via email or forms.</span></strong></p><h2><strong><span>12. International Data Transfers</span></strong></h2><p><strong><span>Our servers and service providers may be located in the </span><span>United States</span><span>, </span><span>Europe</span><span>, or other regions. If you are accessing the site from outside these areas, your data may be transferred across international borders.</span></strong></p><p><strong><span>We ensure all data transfers comply with applicable law, including </span><span>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs)</span><span> or other lawful mechanisms recognized under </span><span>GDPR</span><span>.</span></strong></p><h2><strong><span>13. Changes to This Privacy Policy</span></strong></h2><p><strong><span>We may update this policy from time to time to reflect changes in law, technology, or our services. When we do, we’ll update the “Effective Date” at the top of the page.</span></strong></p><p><strong><span>We encourage users to review this page periodically. Continued use of the Website after changes means you accept the updated policy.</span></strong></p><h2><strong><span>14. Contact Us</span></strong></h2><p><strong><span>For any questions, concerns, or data requests, you may contact us via:</span></strong></p><p><strong><span>Email:</span><span> privacy@playvio.io</span><span><br></span><span> </span><span>Mailing Address:</span><span><br></span><span> PlayVio Media</span><span><br></span><span> 123 Arcade Lane</span><span><br></span><span> Los Angeles, CA 90001</span><span><br></span><span> USA</span></strong></p><p><strong><span>Thank you for trusting </span><a href=\"https://playvio.io\"><span>PlayVio.io</span></a><span>. We’re committed to keeping your data safe, your experience fun, and your rights respected.</span></strong></p><p></p>		', '2025-11-17 03:36:50', '2025-11-17 03:36:50');

